org.openntf.calendars

Interface CalendarRangeInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CalendarRange, CalendarSet

    public interface CalendarRangeInterface
extends Serializable
    Interface for a pair of two Calendar objects specifying a range of time.

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Indicates if this CalendarRange object is valid. Rules for determing if a CalendarRange object is valid are as follows:
        • The First calendar object in the range must not be null
        • The Last calendar object in the range must not be null
        • The Last calendar object may not represent a date / time which is PRIOR to the First calendar object (they may be equal)
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the CalendarRange object is valid

      • contains

        boolean contains(Calendar calendar)
        Returns true if this set contains the specified element. More formally, returns true if and only if this set contains Calendar entry e such that (calendar==null ? false : calendar.equals(e)).
        Parameters:
        calendar - element whose presence in this CalendarRange is to be tested
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if this CalendarRange contains the specified element.

      • contains

        boolean contains(Object object)
        Returns true if this object contains a Calendar-Covertable object for the specified object. A Calendar-Convertable object is any object which can be converted to a Calendar. More formally, returns true if and only if for a Calendar object o constructed from object; this CalendarRange contains contains a Calendar entry e such that (o==null ? false : o.equals(e)).
        Parameters:
        object - the object from which to construct a Calendar object to test against members of this object
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if this object contains a Calender object for the specified object.

      • isInRange

        boolean isInRange(Object object)
        Tests a Calendar-Convertable Object to determine if it falls within the range of Calendar entries within this object. A Calendar-Convertable object is any object which can be converted to a Calendar. Returns false if the specifieds Object is null. Performs an inclusive test, returns true if the specified Object is equal to either the first or last entry.
        Parameters:
        object - Object to test
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the Object falls within this object's range.

      • isInRange

        boolean isInRange(Object object,
                  boolean inclusive)
        Tests a Calendar-Convertable Object to determine if it falls within the range of Calendar entries within this object. A Calendar-Convertable object is any object which can be converted to a Calendar. Returns false if the specifieds Object is null. Conditionally performs an inclusive test.
        Parameters:
        object - Object to test
        inclusive - Flag indicating to include begin and end as valid dates for checking.
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if the Object falls within this object's range.

      • getIntersection

        CalendarRange getIntersection(CalendarRange cr)
        Tests a CalendarRange object to determine if there is an intersection with this object's Range. Note this tests the RANGE encompassed by this object, not just specific entry instances. NOTE both objects MUST be valid (non-null values for first and last entries) Performs an inclusive test, the first and last entries included.
        Parameters:
        calendarrange - Object to test for intersection
        Returns:
        A new CalendarRange object encompassing the intersection between this and the the specified object.

      • isIntersectionExists

        boolean isIntersectionExists(CalendarRange cr)
        Tests a CalendarRange object to determine if there is an intersection with this object's Range. Note this tests the RANGE encompassed by this object, not just specific entry instances. NOTE both objects MUST be valid (non-null values for first and last entries) Performs an inclusive test, the first and last entries included.
        Parameters:
        calendarrange - Object to test for intersection
        Returns:
        Flag indicating if an intersection exists between this and the specified object.
